    <div class="container"> <!--SEE THIS DIV-->
        <h1>HTML Frames</h1>
        <hr>
        <p>An iframe is used to display a web page within a web page.</p>
        <iframe src="demo.html" height="300" width="1000"></iframe><br><br>
        <h1>Iframe Syntax</h1>
        <hr>
        <p>An HTML iframe is defined with the <code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code> tag:</p>
        <br>
        <div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh" style="background-color: white;padding: 10px;">
            <span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>iframe<span style="color:red"> src<span
                        style="color:mediumblue">="<em>URL</em>"</span></span><span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span><span
                style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>/iframe<span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span>
        </div> <!-- how did I get this??
        
        Simple visit w3 schools and copt the code wala portion wahan se. Use inspect element(ctrl+shift+i) -->
        <br>
        <p>The <code>src</code> attribute specifies the URL (web address) of the inline frame page.</p>
        <br>
        <h1>Iframe - Set Height and Width</h1>
        <hr>
        <p>
                Use the <code><!--You would've notied those red texts with background grey. You can do that with <code></code> tags. (Use it wisely as it has been given in w3 schools --> height</code> and <code> width</code>  attributes to specify the size of the iframe.

                The attribute values are specified in pixels by default, but they can also be in percent (like "80%").
        </p><br>
        <div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
                <span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>iframe<span style="color:red"> src<span style="color:mediumblue">="demo_iframe.htm"</span> height<span style="color:mediumblue">="200"</span> width<span style="color:mediumblue">="300"</span></span><span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span><span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>/iframe<span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span> </div><!-- how did I get this??
        
                    Simple visit w3 schools and copt the code wala portion wahan se. Use inspect element(ctrl+shift+i) -->
        <br>
        <h1>Iframe - Remove the Border</h1>
        <hr>
        <p>
                By default, an iframe has a border around it.

                To remove the border, add the <code>style</code>attribute and use the CSS <code>border</code> property:
        </p>
        <br>
        <div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
                <span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>iframe<span style="color:red"> src<span style="color:mediumblue">="demo_iframe.htm"</span> style<span style="color:mediumblue">="border:none;"</span></span><span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span><span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>/iframe<span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span> </div><!-- how did I get this??
        
                    Simple visit w3 schools and copt the code wala portion wahan se. Use inspect element(ctrl+shift+i) -->
            <br>
        <h1>Iframe - Target for a Link</h1>
        <hr>
        <p>An iframe can be used as the target frame for a link.

                The <code>target</code> attribute of the link must refer to the <code>name</code> attribute of the iframe:</p>
                <br>
                <div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
                        <span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>iframe<span style="color:red"> src<span style="color:mediumblue">="demo_iframe.htm"</span> name<span style="color:mediumblue">="iframe_a"</span></span><span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span><span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>/iframe<span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span><br><br>
                        <span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>p<span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span><span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>a<span style="color:red"> href<span style="color:mediumblue">="https://www.w3schools.com"</span> target<span style="color:mediumblue">="iframe_a"</span></span><span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span>W3Schools.com<span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>/a<span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span><span style="color:brown"><span style="color:mediumblue">&lt;</span>/p<span style="color:mediumblue">&gt;</span></span>
                        </div><!-- how did I get this??
        
                            Simple visit w3 schools and copt the code wala portion wahan se. Use inspect element(ctrl+shift+i) -->
            <br>
